page.title: 02Houses in March
page.content: There is a wide range of housing in our area.Many properties close to our school are{semidetached houses}and {detached bungalows.}A few bungalows are quite old and do not have garages. { Near March Railway Station}there is a detached house, built{in 1929.}It has pretty eaves.{Station Road}has some terraced houses,built in{1899,}and {there are three sets of old terraces {in groups of twelve in Norwood Road. {Most of the terraced}housing was the result of the railway boom.In{County {Road are terraced houses in groups of {four,built in 1929,}and only one new house,built in 1984. In {Russel Avenue,}some owners have bought their{council houses.}They have put in UPVC windows and doors, built walls, put up shutters and built porches and extensions.
